\begin{abstract}
A relevant result by Sneddon on an identity on series involving the zeros of Bessel functions of the first kind is derived by an alternative method based on Laplace transforms. Our method leads to a 
Bernstein function of time, expressed by Dirichlet series, that allows us  to recover Sneddon's result. We also consider another method arriving at  the same  result based on a relevant formula by Calogero.

\end{abstract}

